  "prompt": "What do people in Quora get by giving answers that get much upvotes?",
  "response": "People on Quora get a few things from giving answers that get a lot of upvotes:\n\n*   **Sense of Satisfaction and Recognition:** Many people answer questions on Quora simply because they enjoy sharing their knowledge and helping others. Getting a lot of upvotes validates their effort and provides a sense of satisfaction that their answer was helpful or insightful. It's a form of positive reinforcement.\n\n*   **Increased Visibility and Credibility:** Upvotes boost the visibility of an answer, making it more likely to be seen by more people. This can lead to the answerer being perceived as a knowledgeable and credible source on the topic.\n\n*   **Improved Quora Stats/Metrics:** Quora tracks various statistics for its users, including the number of upvotes they've received, the number of people who have viewed their answers, etc. Having a high number of upvotes can improve these stats, which some users find motivating. Some Quora users see improving their stats as a sort of game or challenge.\n\n*   **Potential for Quora Partner Program Revenue:** Quora has a partner program that allows users to earn money by asking questions. While answering questions doesn't directly generate revenue, having a high profile and a large following due to highly upvoted answers could indirectly benefit someone in the partner program, as their questions might be seen by more people.\n\n*   **Learning and Engagement:** Answering questions and receiving feedback (through upvotes and comments) can be a learning experience. It allows users to refine their understanding of a topic and engage in constructive discussions with others.\n\n*   **Building a Personal Brand:** For some professionals, Quora can be a platform to build their personal brand and establish themselves as experts in their field. High-quality, upvoted answers can attract attention from potential clients, employers, or collaborators.\n\nIn summary, the benefits of getting upvotes on Quora are primarily related to personal satisfaction, recognition, increased visibility, and the potential for professional advancement.",
